Subject: [PATCH] Create parent reference columns for collection indexes

Content Blocks generates a parent uid index for Collection child tables via
the `foreign_field` TCA setting. When the child table is created from scratch,
the generated SQL can include `KEY parent_uid (foreign_table_parent_uid)`
without also declaring the `foreign_table_parent_uid` column. MariaDB then
rejects the database update with "Key column 'foreign_table_parent_uid'
doesn't exist in table".

Emit parent reference column definitions alongside their indexes, matching how
foreign_match_fields helper columns are already generated.

Affected file:
  Classes/Generator/SqlGenerator.php

--- a/Classes/Generator/SqlGenerator.php
+++ b/Classes/Generator/SqlGenerator.php
@@ -80,6 +80,7 @@ protected function handleParentReferences(TableDefinition $tableDefinition): arr
             if (isset($parentTcaConfig['foreign_table_field'])) {
                 $foreignTableName = $parentTcaConfig['foreign_table_field'];
                 $index[] = $foreignTableName;
+                $fields[] = $foreignTableName;
             }
             // The foreign_match_fields fields are automatically added, so that feature "shareAcrossFields" works.
             foreach ($parentTcaConfig['foreign_match_fields'] ?? [] as $foreignMatchField => $foreignMatchValue) {
@@ -89,6 +90,7 @@ protected function handleParentReferences(TableDefinition $tableDefinition): arr
             if (isset($parentTcaConfig['foreign_field'])) {
                 $foreignField = $parentTcaConfig['foreign_field'];
                 $index[] = $foreignField;
+                $fields[] = $foreignField;
             }
             $indexes[] = $index;
         }
